IIRC, service workers aren't possible due to the iframe?
Can't really remember xD

WebWorkers work for sure tho as I've used them in the new ThunderWaveX but you have to load the script through a different method:

```javascript
page.cmd(
	'fileGet',
	['Path/To/WebWorkerScript.js', 'text'],
	f => {
		const url = URL.createObjectURL(
			new Blob([f], {
				type: 'text/javascript'
			})
		);

		const worker = new Worker(url);
	}
);
```

And I think you have to be on a secure host (e.g. `localhost` in chrome and in firefox you have to enable it IIRC) to be able to use them (both types of workers)
